Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function, likely nephropathy. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes less likely. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation for possible chronic kidney disease and further assessment of underlying etiology.
